This instructable describes an A2 plotter made from low cost aluminium extrusion, a piece of particle board, two NEMA17 stepper motors, and a few belts and pulleys.The plotter is:high resolution (80 steps/mm),            fast,            low-cost,            and scaleableThe plotter has an on-board interpreter that recognizes the g-code output from "Inkscape" .Metal work is simple ... all you need is a hacksaw, three drills, a rat-tail file, and a screwdriver.12 October 2017:An improved pen-lift is described in instructable https://www.instructables.com/id/CNC-Pen-Lift/16 November 2017:Bluetooth is added in instructable https://www.instructables.com/id/Add-Bluetooth-to-...Z-axis control is added in instuctable https://www.instructables.com/id/CNC-Pen-and-Wash-...17 March 2018:GRBL (optional) installed in instructable https://www.instructables.com/id/How-to-Control-a-...

